TRADING PROTOCOLS SUBJECT: DAY TRADING & SWING TRADING USING
PLANETARY TIMING
Now we get surgical. The macro reports gave you the big picture. This report gives you the
actual daily and weekly operating system — the cockpit you sit in every morning before you
open a chart on your screen.
Understand the hierarchy first. There are three time layers in astrological trading. Each one
nests inside the other.
MACRO (Monthly-Yearly) → Jupiter, Saturn, Rahu/Ketu transits. This is your direction bias. Are
you in a bull environment or bear environment overall. You never fight this layer.
SWING (Days to Weeks) → Sun and Mars transits + Lunar cycle (New/Full Moon + Tithis). This
is your trade setup window. Where entries and exits are staged.
DAY TRADE (Hours) → The Moon's Nakshatra transit + Hora (Planetary Hour) system. This is
your precise entry and exit trigger. Down to the hour.
Let's build all three layers into a working daily protocol.
LAYER 1 — THE MACRO BIAS (Check Once Per Month)
Before you trade a single day, you need to know what environment you are operating in. Open
your ephemeris. Answer these four questions:
Question 1 — Where is Jupiter? Jupiter in Air signs (Gemini, Libra, Aquarius) = speculative
bull bias. Risk assets, crypto, growth stocks favored. Lean long overall. Jupiter in Earth signs
(Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn) = value and consolidation. Commodities, physical assets favored
over speculation. Jupiter retrograde = prices inflate artificially in whatever sign it occupies. The
inflation is real but it will reverse when Jupiter goes direct. Trade the reversal.
Question 2 — Where is Saturn? Saturn in Earth = slow grinding bear pressure on banking,
real estate, traditional assets. Reduce leverage. Protect capital. Saturn in Air = rapid violent
liquidations are possible. Market moves fast in both directions. Good for day traders, dangerous
for overleveraged swing traders. Saturn retrograde = delays and false recoveries. Bounces that
look like bull reversals are traps. Do not chase.
Question 3 — Are Mars and Saturn in Samasaptaka (180° opposition)? If yes across
Taurus/Scorpio or Leo/Aquarius = global financial panic window is active. This is a defensive
mode. Reduce all positions. The physics favor sharp destructive moves. This can last weeks.
Question 4 — Is Rahu or Ketu receiving Jupiter's gaze (aspect)? Jupiter aspecting Rahu =
bubble inflation phase. Speculative assets explode upward. Ride it but set hard exits. Jupiter
aspecting Ketu = dissolution phase. Old structures crumbling. Avoid longs in legacy assets.
Write your macro bias down as a single sentence each month. Example: "Jupiter in Gemini
(bullish Air), Saturn in Pisces (watery deception), no Samasaptaka active, Rahu in Pisces with
no Jupiter aspect = cautiously bullish on speculative assets, beware false signals and liquidity
traps." That sentence governs your entire month's posture.
LAYER 2 — THE SWING TRADE SETUP (Check Weekly)
Swing trades run 2 days to 3 weeks. The instruments for this layer are the Lunar Cycle (Tithis),
Mars transits, and the Full Moon / New Moon Axis.
THE TITHI (Lunar Day) TRADING SYSTEM
The Moon completes a full cycle every 29.5 days through 30 Tithis (lunar days). Each group has
a distinct trading energy. This is your weekly calendar.
High Volatility Tithis — Avoid new entries, tighten stops: Ashtami (8th Tithi) — Conflict
energy. Mars Tithi. Unexpected aggressive moves. Do not enter new positions. This is a
stop-hunt day. Chaturdashi (14th Tithi) — The day before Full or New Moon. Maximum tension.
Reversals often occur here or the next day. Amavasya (New Moon / 30th Tithi) — Complete
darkness. Uncertainty peak. Rahu energy dominates. Crypto in particular makes its sharpest
irrational moves on or within 24 hours of Amavasya. Purnima (Full Moon / 15th Tithi) —
Maximum emotional energy. Market often makes a swing high or swing low within 2 days of Full
Moon. Watch for reversal, not continuation.
Low Volatility, High Clarity Tithis — Best for entering new positions: Dwitiya/Tritiya
(2nd–3rd Tithi) — Right after New Moon. Fresh energy. Momentum building. Trend entries here
have the cleanest follow-through. Panchami (5th Tithi) — Jupiter's Tithi. Expansion. Long bias,
especially on growth and speculative assets. Dashami (10th Tithi) — Mercury's Tithi. Fast
moving information-driven markets. Good for intraday setups. Ekadashi (11th Tithi) — One of
the most auspicious Tithis in Vedic tradition. Gains made on this day tend to sustain. Financial
initiations on Ekadashi historically hold.
Practical Swing Trade Protocol using Tithis: Every Sunday night, pull up a Panchang app
(Drik Panchang is free) and look at the week's Tithis. Mark the Ashtami, Chaturdashi, Full Moon,
and New Moon days as NO ENTRY / MANAGE EXISTING POSITIONS ONLY. Mark the
Dwitiya, Panchami, and Ekadashi days as ENTRY WINDOWS. This alone will eliminate a large
percentage of bad entry timing.
THE MARS SIGN TRANSIT — THE 6–8 WEEK SWING BIAS
Mars changes signs approximately every 6–8 weeks. Each sign it enters shifts the swing trade
environment:
Mars in Fire signs (Aries, Leo, Sagittarius) = aggressive, fast, volatile. Momentum trades.
Breakouts work. Cut losers fast. Everything moves faster than expected in both directions. Mars
in Earth signs (Taurus, Virgo, Capricorn) = slow grind moves. Mean reversion setups work better
than breakouts. Commodities and physical assets get the Mars energy. Mars in Water signs
(Cancer, Scorpio, Pisces) = deceptive. Emotional markets. False breakouts everywhere. Mars is
uncomfortable in Water. Reduce size. These periods produce the most confusing price action.
Mars in Air signs (Gemini, Libra, Aquarius) = information-driven volatility. News events
dominate. Gap-and-go moves. Crypto especially hyperactive.
When Mars changes signs — the first 3 days after ingress are the highest volatility
window. The market is repricing to the new Mars energy. Either a strong directional move or a
sharp reversal happens at every Mars sign change. Mark these dates in your calendar at the
start of every month.
LATTA KICKS — YOUR WEEKLY HIGH-IMPACT DAY IDENTIFIER
Every week, calculate Mars and Saturn's current Nakshatra. Count 3 forward from Mars's
position — that Nakshatra is receiving a Mars Latta. Count 8 forward from Saturn's position —
that Nakshatra is receiving a Saturn Latta.
Now check: What day does the Moon transit those Latta-struck Nakshatras?
That specific day = highest probability of a violent market swing. Not necessarily up or down
— but a decisive move. Day traders want this day. Swing traders want to be positioned before
this day if the macro bias confirms the direction, and flat if the macro is ambiguous.
The Moon transits one Nakshatra roughly every 24 hours. So you get 27 daily Nakshatra
transits per lunar month. Of those 27, the ones receiving active Latta from Mars or Saturn are
your High Impact Days. Typically 2–4 per week qualify. Those are the days you show up fully
alert. The other days you manage existing positions and stay small.
LAYER 3 — THE DAY TRADE ENTRY (The Hora System —
Hourly Precision)
This is the deepest level. The Hora system divides every day into 24 one-hour planetary
segments, each ruled by one of the 7 classical planets. The sequence runs: Sun, Venus,
Mercury, Moon, Saturn, Jupiter, Mars — then repeats.
The Day Lord determines where the sequence starts:
● Sunday starts with Sun Hora
● Monday starts with Moon Hora
● Tuesday starts with Mars Hora
● Wednesday starts with Mercury Hora
● Thursday starts with Jupiter Hora
● Friday starts with Venus Hora
● Saturday starts with Saturn Hora
The Trading Rules per Hora:
Sun Hora — Confidence, authority, gold. Good for large-cap stocks. Gold entries. Leadership
moves. The market tends to be decisive during Sun Hora. Clear direction.
Moon Hora — Emotional, reactive. Good for crypto entries during bull runs (Moon amplifies the
collective emotion). Silver plays. Volatile and quick. Good for scalping, not for holding.
Mars Hora — Aggressive, fast. The most dangerous Hora for inexperienced traders. Breakouts
happen here but so do false breakouts. If you have a confirmed setup with macro and swing
alignment — enter on Mars Hora for maximum momentum. If you don't have confirmation —
stay out. Mars Hora punishes hesitation and rewards decisiveness equally.
Mercury Hora — Information processing, speed, data. Best Hora for reading charts, adjusting
strategy, executing quick scalps. Tech stocks, information sector moves. Good for
communication-heavy assets.
Jupiter Hora — The wealth Hora. Consistently the best Hora for entering positions you intend
to hold. The market tends to expand during Jupiter Hora. Long entries made during Jupiter Hora
in a bull environment have the highest success rate. In a bear environment, Jupiter Hora
produces the strongest bear market rallies — which are traps.
Venus Hora — Luxury, pleasure, ease. Good for lifestyle stocks, entertainment, beauty sector.
Crypto tends to have pleasant low-volatility moves during Venus Hora. Not aggressive. Good for
adding to existing winning positions.
Saturn Hora — The most dangerous Hora. This is when the market tends to stagnate, trap, or
reverse against you. Saturn Hora is for closing positions, taking profits, and reviewing your
book. Not entering. Saturn Hora new entries have statistically poor outcomes because Saturn
delays and restricts whatever it touches. Many experienced traders simply do not trade during
Saturn Hora.
Practical Day Trade Protocol: Every morning before market open, calculate the day's Hora
sequence starting from your local sunrise (use a Hora app or Drik Panchang). Identify the
Jupiter and Mars Horas for the trading session. Those are your primary entry windows —
provided the Moon's current Nakshatra is not in an afflicted Vedha state. Cross-reference with
the day's Tithi. If it's an Ashtami or Chaturdashi day, even Jupiter Hora setups carry higher risk.
Reduce size accordingly.
